Description: Terminal-based BitTorrent client written in Rust
 superseedr is a feature-rich BitTorrent client with a terminal user interface
 built using Ratatui. It implements the full BitTorrent protocol including:
 .
  * Multi-torrent download and seeding support
  * Tracker, DHT, and PEX peer discovery
  * Magnet link support with metadata download
  * Rarest-first piece selection with endgame mode
  * Tit-for-tat choking algorithm with optimistic unchoking
  * Interactive TUI with real-time network graphs
  * Configurable bandwidth limits and resource management
  * Cross-platform configuration and state persistence
